  "prompt": "Is calibri with font size 9 good for resume?",
  "response": "Using Calibri with a font size of 9 for a resume is generally not recommended. While Calibri is a modern and legible font, a font size of 9 might be too small for comfortable reading, particularly for hiring managers who quickly scan resumes. \n\nHere are some tips for font selection and size on a resume:\n\n1. **Font Size**: A font size between 10.5 and 12 is typically preferred for the body text on resumes. This ensures that the text is readable while maintaining a professional appearance.\n\n2. **Font Choice**: While Calibri is acceptable, you might also consider other professional fonts like Arial, Times New Roman, or Garamond, depending on the style of the resume and the industry.\n\n3. **Whitespace**: Ensure there's enough white space on the page to make the document easy to read. This can include appropriate margins, spacing between sections, and bullet points for lists.\n\n4. **Consistency**: Whatever font and size you choose, be consistent throughout the document.\n\nIn summary, stick to a font size of 10.5 to 12 for a clean, professional look that enhances readability.",
